{
  "stem": "7832.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every time I was able to get to the latrine or go anywhere I would tear off a piece of my clothing and use it as toilet paper.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was very careful what I was using my piece of clothing for.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I had to tear off a piece of string to tie up my arm.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was afraid to tell anybody, because that was an instant crematorium trip, if something was wrong with you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was afraid to tell anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I tied up my arm in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I went-- I took my life in my hands and I went out of the barrack to the back door.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "See, the barracks had two entrances.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the back-- the same doors.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Only the back door very seldom opened, because they-- they had you going out one door all the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But it was always a little bit-- it was never shut tight because it wasn't constructed that well.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I-- I went-- I went to the back door, and I didn't open the door, but I put my arm out through the door, through the crack of the door, into the mud on the-- on the ground.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I stayed there until daybreak.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then at daybreak I went to [INAUDIBLE] appell from there, and the line was down from the cold-- from the mud-- from the-- you know?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then that was gone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because see, the next day, they took us back to see how it is.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if they would have seen that, they would have sent me to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was so thankful that I had no longer a red line going up my arm.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then they examined our- but my finger was damaged.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
